","Theme_cosmos_descr_22":"Jupiter is so large that it could fit all the other planets of our solar system inside.","Theme_cosmos_descr_23":"19% of the Sun\'s energy is absorbed by the atmosphere, 47% reaches the Earth, and 34% bounces back into space.","Theme_cosmos_descr_24":"If Saturn was placed in water it would float. The average density of Saturn is half that of water.","Theme_cosmos_descr_25":"The highest temperature on the Moon is 117°C. The lowest temperature is -164°C.","Theme_cosmos_descr_26":"The highest mountain on the Moon is 11.5 kilometers","Theme_cosmos_descr_27":"The Moon\'s diameter is 3476 kilometers.","Theme_cosmos_descr_28":"The Moon is 80 times lighter than the Earth","Theme_cosmos_descr_29":"Venus\' period of revolution around its axis (is around 243 Earth days). That\'s more than it takes the planet to orbit around the Sun (around 225 days). That\'s why Venus\' \\"day\\" is longer than a year.","Theme_cosmos_descr_3":"Around 40 new stars appear in our galaxy every year","Theme_cosmos_descr_30":"Uranus was the first planet discovered with a telescope","Theme_cosmos_descr_31":"Ganymede is the planet Jupiter\'s biggest satellite. It\'s bigger in size than the planet Mercury.","Theme_cosmos_descr_32":"Every year, the distance between the Moon and the Earth increases by 4 centimeters","Theme_cosmos_descr_33":"As the Moon spins on its axis, the same side constantly faces the Earth","Theme_cosmos_descr_34":"The Sun\'s brightness has grown by one percent over the last century.","Theme_cosmos_descr_35":"Our planet is over 4.5 billion years old. Recent research suggests that the Earth is only slightly younger than the Sun, appearing only 10 million years later","Theme_cosmos_descr_36":"The gravitational forces between Earth and the Moon create some interesting effects. The most interesting effect is the sea tides.","Theme_cosmos_descr_37":"The Moon looks bigger near the horizon than it does from tall heights. This is an optical illusion for which there\'s still no definite answer.","Theme_cosmos_descr_38":"Ganymede, Jupiter\'s moon, is the biggest satellite of all of the Solar System\'s planets.","Theme_cosmos_descr_39":"Jupiter has at least 63 moons. The biggest of them--Io, Europa, Ganymede, and Callisto--were discovered by Gallileo Galilei in 1610.","Theme_cosmos_descr_4":"The Betelgeuse star has a diameter larger than the Earth\'s orbit around the Sun","Theme_cosmos_descr_40":"The wind\'s speed on Jupiter can surpass 600 km/hr.","Theme_cosmos_descr_41":\'&lt;a href="https://yandex.ru/search/?text=solar system" target="_blank" class="b-foot-decor__link"&gt;the Solar System&lt;/a&gt; is a planetary system consisting of a central star (the Sun), the big planets that orbit the Sun and their moons; as well as many small planets, comets, and meteoroids.\',"Theme_cosmos_descr_42":\'&lt;a href="https://yandex.ru/search/?text=planet venus" target="_blank" class="b-foot-decor__link"&gt;Venus&lt;/a&gt; — the second planet from the sun in our Solar System. It has an orbit of 224.7 Earth days.\',"Theme_cosmos_descr_43":\'&lt;a href="https://yandex.ru/search/?text=planet earth" target="_blank" class="b-foot-decor__link"&gt;Earth&lt;/a&gt; — the third planet from the Sun in our Solar System. It is the largest in diameter, mass and density among terrestrial planets.\',"Theme_cosmos_descr_44":\'&lt;a href="https://yandex.ru/search/?text=planet mars" target="_blank" class="b-foot-decor__link"&gt;Mars&lt;/a&gt; — the fourth planet from the Sun in our Solar System. It belongs to the terrestrial planet group and is of comparatively small mass and size, with a fairly high average density.\',"Theme_cosmos_descr_45":\'&lt;a href="https://yandex.ru/search/?text=planet jupiter" target="_blank" class="b-foot-decor__link"&gt;Jupiter&lt;/a&gt; — the fifth planet from the Sun, the biggest planet in the Solar System. It\\\'s diameter is 11.1 times bigger than the diameter of Earth.\',"Theme_cosmos_descr_46":\'&lt;a href="https://yandex.ru/search/?text=planet saturn" target="_blank" class="b-foot-decor__link"&gt;Saturn&lt;/a&gt; — the sixth planet from the Sun and the second largest planet in the Solar System after Jupiter.\',"Theme_cosmos_descr_47":\'&lt;a href="https://yandex.ru/search/?text=uranus" target="_blank" class="b-foot-decor__link"&gt;Uranus&lt;/a&gt; — the seventh planet in the Solar System from the Sun. Uranus is 19.19 astronomical units from the Sun. Its orbit lasts 84.02 years.\',"Theme_cosmos_descr_48":\'&lt;a href="https://yandex.ru/search/?text=planet neptune" target="_blank" class="b-foot-decor__link"&gt;Neptune&lt;/a&gt; — the eighth planet from the Sun in our Solar System. Neptune is 30.06 astronomical units from the Sun. Its orbit takes 164.79 years.\',"Theme_cosmos_descr_49":\'&lt;a href="https://yandex.ru/search/?text=planet pluto" target="_blank" class="b-foot-decor__link"&gt;Pluto&lt;/a&gt; — a drawf planet, discovered February 18, 1930 by the American astronomer Clyde Tombaugh. It was considered the ninth planet of our Solar System until August 24, 2006.\',"Theme_cosmos_descr_5":"The largest lunar crater visible from Earth is called Bailly.","Theme_cosmos_descr_6":"As the Moon spins on its axis, the same side constantly faces the Earth","Theme_cosmos_descr_7":"The highest mountain on the Moon is 11.5 kilometers","Theme_cosmos_descr_8":"The Moon is 80 times lighter than the Earth","Theme_cosmos_descr_9":"The smallest planet in the Solar System is Mercury and the largest is Jupiter","Theme_cosmos_share_text":"Interesting facts about the conquest of the universe right in your inbox","Theme_cosmos_share_title":"The infinite universe in Yandex Mail","Theme_cosmos_share_twitter_text":"The endless expanse of space in Yandex Mail","Theme_dreams_author":\'Illustrator — <a href="http://darianyberg.com/" target="_blank" class="b-foot-decor__author__link">Daria Nyberg</a>\',"Theme_dreams_save_bg":"show only this background","Theme_fenerbahce_share_text":"Fenerbahce! Get the yellow and